HEADWORD: Gymnophthalmata
<hw>Gym`noph*thal"ma*ta</hw>
<pr>(j⟦icr⟧m`n⟦ocr⟧f*th⟦acr⟧l"m⟦adot⟧*t⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>gymno`s</grk> naked + <grk>'ofqalmo`s</grk> the
eye.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A group of acalephs, including the
naked-eyed medus⟦ae⟧; the hydromedus⟦ae⟧. Most of them are known to be
the free-swimming progeny (gonophores) of hydroids.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

